    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="695"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6925: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received May 24—5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>345. Following from Admiral McCully, Sevastopol:</p>
                <p>54. May 22, 10 p.m. On May 20 and 21 visited Crimea front accompanying General
                    Wrangel. Positions occupied by his forces have been greatly strengthened. Troops
                    are in excellent condition and have good spirit. However there is no such
                    concentration near front as might indicate early offensive operations by Wrangel
                    forces.</p>
                <p>Mr. A. T. Burri<note n="14" xml:id="d695fn14">Vice consul at
                        Constantinople.</note> arrived in Sevastopol May 21, noon, under
                    instructions from United States High Commissioner, Constantinople. McCully.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
